The '''grey thornbill''', '''ashy gerygone''' or '''mountain gerygone''' ('''''Acanthiza cinerea''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Acanthizidae]]. It is found in the [[New Guinea Highlands]]. Its [[habitat]] includes [[subtropical]] and [[tropical]] moist [[montane forest]]s.

